<emphasis id="B9375F7AFFFBEC0DFF27EEEFFE89FB47" bold="true" box="[189,334,1182,1208]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Description</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFC8368FFFBEC0DFF27EEBCFD43FB18" blockId="26.[189,644,1228,1255]" box="[189,644,1228,1255]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
LENGTH. Body 10.0 mm, wing 
<quantity id="4CBB2E8DFFFBEC0DFDB9EEBDFD47FB18" box="[547,640,1228,1255]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.5" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" unit="mm" value="7.5">7.5 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFC8368FFFBEC0DFF27EF7FFAB0FA04" blockId="26.[189,1399,1294,1531]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
HEAD (
<figureCitation id="13789FEDFFFBEC0DFE95EF7FFEB6FAD7" box="[271,369,1294,1320]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="6.[189,232,1822,1848]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,518,1778]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[189,1399,518,1778]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Fig. 2. Megatrigon spp., head, dorsal view. A. Megatrigon argenteus (Walker, 1852) comb. nov. (♁). B. M. argentifrons sp. nov. (♁). C. M. argentimaculatus sp. nov. (♁). D. M. magnicornis sp. nov. (♁). E–F. M.natalensissp. nov.(arrow =postocellarspot)(♁).G.M.sexmaculatus sp. nov.(♁).H. M.apiformis sp. nov. (♁). I. M. cooksoni sp. nov. (♁). J. M. immaculatus sp. nov. (♁). K. M. ochreatus (Hull, 1964) comb. nov. (♁). L. M. tabanoides sp. nov. (♁). M. M. jacobi (Hervé-Bazin, 1913) comb. nov. (♁). N. M. nivalis (Hull, 1964) comb. nov. (♀). Symbol: x = postocellar spot." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3849882" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3849882/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Figs 2K</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13789FEDFFFBEC0DFEE5EF7FFE5BFAD7" box="[383,412,1294,1320]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="7.[188,231,1822,1848]" captionTargetBox="[233,1359,267,1781]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[233,1359,267,1781]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Fig. 3. Megatrigon spp., left antenna, lateral view. A. Megatrigon argenteus (Walker, 1852) comb. nov. (♁). B. M. argentifrons sp. nov. (♁). C. M. argentimaculatus sp. nov. (♁). D. M. magnicornis sp. nov. (♁). E. M. natalensis sp. nov. (♁). F. M. sexmaculatus sp. nov. (♁). G. M. apiformis sp. nov. (♁). H. M. cooksoni sp. nov. (♁). I. M. immaculatus sp. nov. (♁). J. M. ochreatus (Hull, 1964) comb. nov. (♁). K. M. tabanoides sp. nov. (♁). L. M. jacobi (Hervé-Bazin, 1913) comb. nov. (♁). M. M. nivalis (Hull, 1964) comb. nov. (♀)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3849886" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3849886/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">3J</figureCitation>
). Face largely microtrichiose: microtrichiose stripes along eye margins long, wide, especially at the level below antennae where joined median facial stripe and narrow oblique stripe; face and gena wider than in 
<taxonomicName id="4C43F8EBFFFBEC0DFE40EF24FDB1FA91" authorityName="Doczkal &amp; Radenković &amp; Lyneborg &amp; Pape" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Walker" baseAuthorityYear="1852" box="[474,630,1365,1390]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Megatrigon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="argenteus" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis id="B9375F7AFFFBEC0DFE40EF24FDB1FA91" box="[474,630,1365,1390]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">M. argenteus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A204E201FFFBEC0DFDE5EF25FCC2FA90" box="[639,773,1364,1391]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, gena 1.5 × as wide as postpedicel (in 
<taxonomicName id="4C43F8EBFFFBEC0DFB41EF24FAB0FA91" authorityName="Doczkal &amp; Radenković &amp; Lyneborg &amp; Pape" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Walker" baseAuthorityYear="1852" box="[1243,1399,1365,1390]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Megatrigon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="argenteus" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis id="B9375F7AFFFBEC0DFB41EF24FAB0FA91" box="[1243,1399,1365,1390]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">M. argenteus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A204E201FFFBEC0DFF27EF06FE86FA6D" box="[189,321,1399,1426]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
gena and postpedicel of equal width); distance between eyes larger than in 
<taxonomicName id="4C43F8EBFFFBEC0DFB40EF09FAB0FA6E" authorityName="Doczkal &amp; Radenković &amp; Lyneborg &amp; Pape" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Walker" baseAuthorityYear="1852" box="[1242,1399,1400,1425]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Megatrigon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="argenteus" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis id="B9375F7AFFFBEC0DFB40EF09FAB0FA6E" box="[1242,1399,1400,1425]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">M. argenteus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A204E201FFFBEC0DFF27EFEBFE86FA4A" box="[189,321,1434,1461]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, 0.19 × width of head; postocular orbit wider than in 
<taxonomicName id="4C43F8EBFFFBEC0DFC2CEFEAFB97FA4B" authorityName="Doczkal &amp; Radenković &amp; Lyneborg &amp; Pape" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Walker" baseAuthorityYear="1852" box="[950,1104,1435,1460]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Megatrigon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="argenteus" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis id="B9375F7AFFFBEC0DFC2CEFEAFB97FA4B" box="[950,1104,1435,1460]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">M. argenteus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A204E201FFFBEC0DFBC2EFEBFB1BFA4A" box="[1112,1244,1434,1461]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, the width of postocular orbit dorsally 0.13 × width of head; postpedicel longer than in 
<taxonomicName id="4C43F8EBFFFBEC0DFB95EFCEFB6FFA27" authorityName="Doczkal &amp; Radenković &amp; Lyneborg &amp; Pape" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Walker" baseAuthorityYear="1852" box="[1039,1192,1471,1496]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Megatrigon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="argenteus" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis id="B9375F7AFFFBEC0DFB95EFCEFB6FFA27" box="[1039,1192,1471,1496]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">M. argenteus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A204E201FFFBEC0DFB34EFCFFAF6FA27" box="[1198,1329,1470,1496]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, 1.7 × as long as deep; 1.7 × as long as pedicel; ocellar triangle equilateral without median longitudinal groove.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFC8368FFFBEC0DFF27EC52FC7CF99F" blockId="26.[189,1398,1570,1632]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">THORAX. Mesoscutum with lateral microtrichiose stripes and traces of prescutellar microtrichia; supraalar setae yellow; mediotergite mostly covered with microtrichia.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFC8368FFFBEC0DFF27ECF9FF38F917" blockId="26.[189,1399,1671,1768]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">WING. Membrane irregulary yellow-brown infuscated, densely covered with microtrichia that is mainly yellow-brown, except white microtrichia along the posterior edge and wing base; costagium with yellow setae.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFC8368FFFBEC0DFF27ED7EFDF5F8B2" blockId="26.[189,1398,1807,1869]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">LEGS. Setae yellow; all tarsi yellow, metatibia almost entirely dark, with white microtrichia in proximal half dorsally that reach the scar.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFC8368FFFBEC0DFF27ED05FBEEF82B" blockId="26.[189,1399,1907,2004]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
ABDOMEN (
<figureCitation id="13789FEDFFFBEC0DFEA7ED02FE54F871" box="[317,403,1907,1934]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[189,232,1822,1848]" captionTargetBox="[241,1346,265,1784]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[241,1346,265,1784]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 1. Megatrigon spp., habitus, dorsal view. A. Megatrigon argenteus (Walker, 1852) comb. nov. (♁). B. M. argentifrons sp. nov. (♁). C. M. argentimaculatus sp. nov. (♁). D. M. magnicornis sp. nov. (♁). E. M. natalensis sp. nov. (♁). F. M. sexmaculatus sp. nov. (♁). G. M. apiformis sp. nov. (♁). H. M. cooksoni sp. nov. (♁). I. M. immaculatus sp. nov. (♁). J. M. ochreatus (Hull, 1964) comb. nov. (♁). K. M. tabanoides sp. nov. (♁). L. M. jacobi (Hervé-Bazin, 1913) comb. nov. (♁). M. M. nivalis (Hull, 1964) comb. nov. (♀)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3849878" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3849878/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Figs 1J</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13789FEDFFFBEC0DFE38ED05FE78F871" box="[418,447,1908,1934]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="11.[189,232,1862,1888]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,265,1837]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[189,1399,265,1837]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Fig. 7. Megatrigon spp., abdomen, dorsal view, ♁. A. Megatrigon argenteus (Walker, 1852) comb. nov. B. M. argentifrons sp. nov. C. M. argentimaculatus sp. nov. D. M. magnicornis sp. nov. E. M. natalensis sp. nov. F. M. sexmaculatus sp. nov. G. M. apiformis sp. nov. H. M. cooksoni sp. nov. I. M. immaculatus sp. nov. J. M. ochreatus (Hull, 1964) comb. nov. K. M. tabanoides sp. nov. L. M. jacobi (Hervé-Bazin, 1913) comb. nov." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3849902" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3849902/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">7J</figureCitation>
). Narrower than in 
